<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2456"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2456-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2456">National ballot initiatives&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">RossMLevin</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">11 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">We should amend the constitution to allow for a national ballot initiative process.  It would allow citizens to address issues that Congress fails to or does so inadequately, such as real campaign finance reform.  This would not get rid of any current aspect of our government, it would just provide another check and balance to the people.<br/><br/>For a proposed amendment, please read:  http://ni4d.us/amendment</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2456" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2456', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2245&topicID=2456')">Comments (7)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2456"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2245">Rulemaking</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=national initiative for democracy">national initiative for democracy</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=ni4d">ni4d</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=amendment">amendment</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=ballot initiative">ballot initiative</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=direct democracy">direct democracy</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2456"></div>
</div></td>
